  "title": "Product Manager (Rewards) – Fintech (Singapore)",
  "description": "<p>We are partnered with a digital asset and cross-border payment firm to hire a <strong>Product Manager </strong>to lead the development of <strong>customer rewards and loyalty features. </strong><br /></p><p>This role will play a key part in driving user acquisition and retention through well-designed promotional mechanics embedded across user and transaction journeys.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Define and execute the product strategy and roadmap for rewards and loyalty features.</li><li>Own the full product lifecycle from discovery and design through development, testing, launch, and iteration, working closely with UI/UX, technology, operations, and compliance teams.</li><li>Design reward mechanics that influence purchasing behaviour while maintaining cost efficiency and sustainable ROI.</li><li>Partner with data and business teams to track performance, analyse effectiveness, and identify optimisation opportunities for promotional features.</li><li>Provide post-launch support, including user education, issue analysis, and continuous product enhancement.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Our Ideal Candidate</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Business Analytics, Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related discipline.</li><li>4+ years of experience in product management or product development, ideally within consumer-facing mobile or web platforms.</li><li>Hands-on experience with Promotion or Marketing products in the digital payment industry.</li><li>Fluency in English and Mandarin is required as this role will work closely with China-based vendors.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Why Join</strong></p><ul><li>Own a high-impact product area that directly influences growth and customer engagement.</li><li>Work within a regulated fintech environment with meaningful scale and real-world complexity.</li><li>Strong autonomy, visibility, and opportunity to shape products from the ground up.</li></ul><p></p><p>Reg. No. R23114042<br />BeathChapman Pte Ltd<br />Licence no. 16S8112</p>",
